%% README

The script plsr_script_fe.m performs explanatory (i.e. in-sample) PLS regression analyses.
It uses leave-one-out cross validation to estimate the optimal number of model components.
Once an optimal component number is identified, the plsr model is fit to the full dataset, and 
confidence intervals are estimated for the model fit and beta weights using bootstrap
resampling. Methods are described in detail in Griffis et al., (2019 -- Cell Reports).

The script plsr_script_oos.m performs predictive (i.e. out-of-sample) PLS regression analyses.
It uses nested cross-validation to select the optimal number of model components for each test case.
It only outputs model fit statistics,and does not perform signficance tests.

The Support_Functions folder and subfolders contain necessary functions,
and must be in your MATLAB path to run the script.

All code is written by me with the exception of the functions in the matlab_nifti folder,
which was obtained from the MATLAB file exchange.

The script can be run as is to get an example weight map.

Joseph Griffis, 2019, Washington University in St Louis